[{'comment_id': 1294998403, 'comment_body': 'Why are we removing this subscriber and observer???
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 15, 19, 1, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rishabh-997', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1295052963, 'comment_body': '@rishabh-997 I was the one who added this code but when unit tests were failing I noticed this was a bug. I replaced it with "execute()" method which returns the immediate result of observable available.
**"fun <T> Observable<T>.execute(): T = this.single().toBlocking().first()"**
Like this I did many refactoring in my earlier written code. 
Regardless the api call is still kept as an observable so that implementers of SDK can implement it in that pattern if wanted.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 15, 20, 0, 13, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'shubhamsgit', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1295890504, 'comment_body': 'So we are blocking the thread till the execution is completed instead of handling in backgraound and wait for results?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 16, 13, 21, 38, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rishabh-997', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1295922657, 'comment_body': "RestApi function gives the result immediately. And the result won't emit any addition to the observale too, since there are no triggers to the restApi function except for once in this ObservationRepository function.

I guess the restApi functions were kept to return observales since It's a good practice to maintain consistency in the codebase, if the majority of codebase uses reactive programming, returning an Observable or a Flow from Retrofit API functions would align well with the overall architecture of the SDK.

So here we are just fetching the immediate result, instead of waiting for more results because there are absolutely zero changes to the result after the initial execution. So, It won't be any worth for the thread to keep waiting.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 16, 13, 40, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'shubhamsgit', 'type': 'User'}]
